[[ Family 
<taxonomicName id="9E75CE3B1858EDD6129621B15F1104F9" family="Cirrhitidae" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Cirrhitidae</taxonomicName>
]]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D2C9304493741BEDCAA284144481B1E9" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="CA706EC7540830E7A526FA85A2811238" pageNumber="1">
The perciform fish family 
<taxonomicName id="A915097CF50DC3FDA38A628BED640EE5" family="Cirrhitidae" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Cirrhitidae</taxonomicName>
is characterized by having 14 pectoral rays, the lower 5 to 7 unbranched and enlarged with the membranes deeply incised; a single dorsal fin of X spines and 11 to 17 soft rays, the fin notched between the spinous and soft portions; membrane at dorsal spine tips with one to several cirri; anal rays III,5-7; 15 principal caudal rays; pelvic rays I,5; opercular spines 2; a fringe of cirri on posterior edge of anterior nostril; margin of preopercle serrate, though often only on upper half (number of serrae increase with age); scales cycloid; gill membranes broadly joined, with a free fold across throat; no swimbladder; 6 branchiostegal rays; and 26 vertebrae. Except for the presence or absence of palatine teeth and except for the reduced size of the canines in the monotypic genus 
<taxonomicName id="C8A6D50B68A49AA8EA1930D77F47B716" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9A5FCAE1-60DB-400B-BFD8-ED47AE93C254" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Oxycirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Oxycirrhites Bleeker 1857:39" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Oxycirrhites</taxonomicName>
, the dentition is essentially the same for all species: an outer row of small incurved canines, the largest in upper jaw at the front, and the largest in the lower jaw as 2 to 4 recurved canines nearly half way back in jaw; a broad dense inner band of villiform teeth at front of jaws, continuing progressively narrower posteriorly in upper jaw; a narrow V-shaped band of small teeth on the vomer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="60878B00ADA3BEBBECBE2AD761CD3F6C" pageNumber="2">
The 
<taxonomicName id="9F17863848B994368491E73B39EBC390" family="Cirrhitidae" pageNumber="2" rank="family">Cirrhitidae</taxonomicName>
is primarily an Indo-Pacific family, with only three of the 33 species occurring in the Atlantic, and only three in the eastern Pacific (two of which are also wideranging in the Indo-Pacific). Most are found in shallow water on coral reefs or rocky substrata, often in areas exposed to surge. When in a surgy area, they use their thickened lower pectoral rays to wedge themselves in place. 
<taxonomicName id="728DB0BF8E2443C6CB3EBA6C02CABEF1" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cyprinocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="polyactis">Cyprinocirrhites polyactis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7E27E82409030F03D941F3FD84BE71B5" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:87C7BC39-0FA3-4417-B201-74341F8AF192" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Oxycirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Oxycirrhites typus Bleeker 1857:40" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="typus">Oxycirrhites typus</taxonomicName>
are exceptions in their usual occurrence in 20-100 m. Cirrhitids feed mainly on benthic crustaceans, occasionally on small fishes. 
<taxonomicName id="F8AA5D418D2D6358C3EB920AB54FA6DF" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cyprinocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="polyactis">C. polyactis</taxonomicName>
feeds well above the substratum on zooplankton, and 
<taxonomicName id="713BB476C0ADC0A3784DCF8D6D5790AC" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:87C7BC39-0FA3-4417-B201-74341F8AF192" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Oxycirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Oxycirrhites typus Bleeker 1857:40" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="typus">O. typus</taxonomicName>
makes short forays into the water column for the larger animals of the zooplankton. At least some of the species (and likely all) are protogynous hermaphrodites (Sadovy &amp; Donaldson 1995).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B78CEB5629C4C88E4FE232AA2232B01E" pageNumber="2">
The generic classification of the 
<taxonomicName id="645548CE0E890B917C21FFE78F07FCC1" family="Cirrhitidae" pageNumber="2" rank="family">Cirrhitidae</taxonomicName>
has a long and confused history which is summarized here:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BF2BDCBAB31668B4A5D437657B21C1A0" pageNumber="2">
<normalizedToken id="FEA653F2C34C14FD5D4C80FD0A5AE46F" originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
(1860) recognized eight genera in the family, only three of which remain in the 
<taxonomicName id="1FDC25C6F52D9F913864AC6144A18BE9" family="Cirrhitidae" pageNumber="2" rank="family">Cirrhitidae</taxonomicName>
today: 
<taxonomicName id="D2305FF530C48792BB5AAA23C18D5A65" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
Cirrhitus 
<normalizedToken id="34749612CAAA38AA697C22BAA507B19A" originalValue="Lacepède">Lacepede</normalizedToken>
</taxonomicName>
(which 
<normalizedToken id="605EB9629E1683469AAB10775A09B499" originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
and most early authors misspelled 
<taxonomicName id="0159DE271384E593F2AC016CB86FFCFC" authority="Lacepède, 1803" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1803" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhites</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="739C336760F53A1E9753E64B82DC384A" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A7B81F0C-1F8D-4339-A46A-3F2F625784D3" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitichthys Bleeker 1857:3, 39" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitichthys Bleeker</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="28A2B22390BAA137827F933A69B72289" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9A5FCAE1-60DB-400B-BFD8-ED47AE93C254" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Oxycirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Oxycirrhites Bleeker 1857:39" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Oxycirrhites Bleeker</taxonomicName>
. The other five genera are now classified in the families Cheilodactylidae and Chironemidae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4DF048FF1BDEB9FC8CED57920035930D" pageNumber="2">
Gill (1862) proposed the genera 
<taxonomicName id="F32E8965251580200EDA519E507C9074" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:6AD3621E-4DC7-4F31-A629-D987B190847D" authority="Gill, 1862" authorityName="Gill" authorityYear="1862" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitopsis Gill 1862:109" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitopsis</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName id="2C991B19A1516365337D6345FBDBA0D8" authority="Lacepède, 1803" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1803" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aureus">Cirrhites aureus Temminck and Schlegel</taxonomicName>
from Japan and 
<taxonomicName id="EEC17B3AFADC6DC45C53ECAE1411CB36" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A7B68FE2-7E5D-4D15-BFA4-EE2E8BD8F54C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Amblycirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Amblycirrhitus Gill 1862:105" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Amblycirrhitus</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName id="A0A5CBC5FC0D8D503142B1D21AABFF0A" authority="Lacepède, 1803" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1803" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciatus">Cirrhites fasciatus Cuvier (1829)</taxonomicName>
for which the type locality was given as 
<normalizedToken id="A119B8800E9156CB3A8A9008D379D719" originalValue="Pondichéry">Pondichery</normalizedToken>
, India.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3C8BB65E1C45D5EC2194E881D70FEC77" pageNumber="2">
Castelnau (1873) described 
<taxonomicName id="D00F22579EAA405EF587E4BB12622EBC" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:68D568EE-EDBF-4AC4-BE6C-33C431C86417" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Neocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Neocirrhites armatus Castelnau 1873:101" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="armatus">Neocirrhites armatus</taxonomicName>
as a new genus and species from northeastern Australia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DEAA7DC8004CCC6D7C0F5034AB21C6A5" pageNumber="2">
Bleeker (1875) treated five genera in the family for the East Indian region, adding 
<taxonomicName id="A17921307BB23FD2ECDAF33B3FD9F2CE" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A7B68FE2-7E5D-4D15-BFA4-EE2E8BD8F54C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Amblycirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Amblycirrhitus Gill 1862:105" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Amblycirrhitus Gill</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="BF3DC46E5904AAFBBB02F02345A79DC4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Paracirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Paracirrhites Bleeker</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="56ED860B33AE4EB46BA5C6E20122C6FD" pageNumber="2">
Steindachner &amp; 
<normalizedToken id="FA801223BD817868ADB4D369D3805B01" originalValue="Döderlein">Doederlein</normalizedToken>
(1884) described 
<taxonomicName id="BB49696B802DB40BE55E93BA21B97C04" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:D6D47312-320D-435B-8DEE-6358F0B05CDC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Paracirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Paracirrhites japonicus Steindachner 1883:25" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="japonicus">Paracirrhites japonicus</taxonomicName>
as a new genus and species from Japan. Noting that their 
<taxonomicName id="331EC694821DD4FEA49EE99103F21F90" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:444182CC-9D9C-4C0C-9E68-4499A1BFF2A6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Paracirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Paracirrhites Steindachner 1883:25" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Paracirrhites</taxonomicName>
was preoccupied by 
<taxonomicName id="518DBA4A23921FE3390255E80A2B7784" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Paracirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Paracirrhites Bleeker</taxonomicName>
, Jordan in Jordan &amp; Herre (1907) proposed the replacement name 
<taxonomicName id="2F02440ED84273A42B358A90A78CF1FE" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2F6B48D5-B8C9-49E2-9393-87E1181F30DA" authority="Jordan, 1907" authorityName="Jordan" authorityYear="1907" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Isobuna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isobuna Jordan 1907:158" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Isobuna</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D4AAE89A94B9971989AF1F0BA7DBAC47" pageNumber="2">
Jenkins (1903) described 
<taxonomicName id="2C2C76D6CF6CBADAEBFE29A1E72A6166" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:5BF2B80F-9DD4-43F0-822F-2E04167F332E" authority="Jenkins, 1903" authorityName="Jenkins" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitoidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitoidea bimacula Jenkins 1903:489" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bimacula">Cirrhitoidea bimacula</taxonomicName>
as a new genus and species from the Hawaiian Islands, unaware that 
<taxonomicName id="0A0C027D37B2F701F9BFA5DBFACB51A2" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A7B68FE2-7E5D-4D15-BFA4-EE2E8BD8F54C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Amblycirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Amblycirrhitus Gill 1862:105" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Amblycirrhitus</taxonomicName>
was available for 
<taxonomicName id="FCBEEF96956E4F4AC9B03ED51F627C21" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:5BF2B80F-9DD4-43F0-822F-2E04167F332E" authority="Jenkins, 1903" authorityName="Jenkins" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitoidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitoidea bimacula Jenkins 1903:489" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bimacula">bimacula</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="34E9165D5EAD7BD02B0042ECBF49315B" pageNumber="2">
Tanaka (1917) created the genus 
<taxonomicName id="A025B37ECDFDF263F249C0323C09630C" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C7E5D36A-EA54-4B8C-8AF3-D40CB52A0CC6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cyprinocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cyprinocirrhites Tanaka 1917:269" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cyprinocirrhites</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName id="2573C7BCAEB2371B32E55E8342CE5C13" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C63C7CF8-5D08-4D7C-88D4-EABC81873844" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitichthys polyactis Bleeker 1874:16" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="polyactis">Cirrhitichthys polyactis Bleeker</taxonomicName>
, surprisingly not named earlier.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5CDCC5DCB9E5FF5C1A16050CBB8F7AB8" pageNumber="2">
Mowbray in Breder (1927) described 
<taxonomicName id="B567C8FA730A709D2F0922BA164F492B" authority="Mowbray, 1927" authorityName="Mowbray" authorityYear="1927" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Pseudocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pinos">Pseudocirrhites pinos</taxonomicName>
as a new genus and species from the Isle of Pines, Cuba.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C922FDB6412E36C42A59B57DE40807F4" pageNumber="2">
Fowler (1938) proposed the new genus 
<taxonomicName id="77A932DFD0192389A847C8B9FF7FCF43" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:4F50B9C7-080F-4BE8-89C1-F7AC756414F2" authority="Fowler, 1938" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1938" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Acanthocirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Acanthocirrhitus Fowler 1938:50" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Acanthocirrhitus</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName id="CE3C6BFE8700F87914E964FBCAF588B2" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oxycephalus">Cirrhitus oxycephalus Bleeker</taxonomicName>
. Realizing that 
<taxonomicName id="6BD84329C8F7C041B00E44400FFEE82D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciatus">Cirrhitus fasciatus Cuvier</taxonomicName>
is preoccupied by 
<taxonomicName id="8F250A76BE05CBE7B0D65108FF4C32A9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciatus">C. fasciatus Bennett (1828)</taxonomicName>
, he provided a replacement name, 
<taxonomicName id="ECBC498718C8FF7373836F80FC7CB604" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:90FD1EF3-9693-49BF-9BE7-6F1701307C7D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Amblycirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Amblycirrhitus indicus Fowler 1938:49" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="indicus">Amblycirrhitus indicus</taxonomicName>
. Randall (2001) has shown that Cuvier’s 
<taxonomicName id="DBBCEB81C3A2E24EF418118D2FF54728" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciatus">C. fasciatus</taxonomicName>
is a specimen of the Atlantic 
<taxonomicName id="15B6227D8285C85D72CF3AE18BD8BB50" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Amblycirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pinos">Amblycirrhitus pinos (Mowbray)</taxonomicName>
, and the type locality of India for 
<taxonomicName id="86EB456CD64FA8C45F61D9EF31089192" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciatus">fasciatus</taxonomicName>
is a locality error for the Atlantic.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EBDE2D6DAEB87761E8229AE0613F4191" pageNumber="2">
Schultz (1943) mistakenly relegated 
<taxonomicName id="393ED79AB7D81602C9F699786B43E468" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C7E5D36A-EA54-4B8C-8AF3-D40CB52A0CC6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cyprinocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cyprinocirrhites Tanaka 1917:269" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cyprinocirrhites</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="0B1D5044503D32453E0D96F23E212CCA" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CC926BD0-C0C7-4941-87D0-54080B379A74" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Neocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Neocirrhites Castelnau 1873:101" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Neocirrhites</taxonomicName>
to the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="98822CAB7495A531228798C69087E352" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A7B81F0C-1F8D-4339-A46A-3F2F625784D3" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitichthys Bleeker 1857:3, 39" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitichthys</taxonomicName>
. He described 
<taxonomicName id="E84818202DF42984BAD91574C92D5C0C" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:610A9D36-A6BE-46D2-9742-4B032894253B" authority="Schultz, 1943" authorityName="Schultz" authorityYear="1943" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Hughichthys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hughichthys Schultz 1943:131, 136" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hughichthys</taxonomicName>
as a new genus for 
<taxonomicName id="283876FE91834693E0E1E4925A4C16FD" authority="Lacepède, 1803" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1803" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanotus">
Cirrhites melanotus 
<normalizedToken id="27DBDA29541847DF05A15330EF346109" originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
</taxonomicName>
, later shown to be a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="8BE59E619B0AC73103F080324B990866" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:68D568EE-EDBF-4AC4-BE6C-33C431C86417" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Neocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Neocirrhites armatus Castelnau 1873:101" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="armatus">Neocirrhites armatus Castelnau</taxonomicName>
. He then placed 
<taxonomicName id="A028A9870B4E2EEA1054BCD218528D48" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3C44979F-8863-4A9F-8276-923CD87238D8" authority="Jenkins, 1903" authorityName="Jenkins" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitoidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitoidea Jenkins 1903:489" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitoidea</taxonomicName>
in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="F18176FEF9E145AB939914DD4F5C45BB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Paracirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Paracirrhites</taxonomicName>
and classified 
<taxonomicName id="F808B8FFD80D8F933E0E691957D56F96" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:5BF2B80F-9DD4-43F0-822F-2E04167F332E" authority="Jenkins, 1903" authorityName="Jenkins" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitoidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitoidea bimacula Jenkins 1903:489" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bimacula">bimacula</taxonomicName>
as a species of 
<taxonomicName id="EA9035648A4FAE289A8E3FAA4B03E3A2" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Paracirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Paracirrhites</taxonomicName>
. He described 
<taxonomicName id="B883A2DE76C8D3FABE64AF6ACF701EF7" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:75A3E3A4-E289-4809-9A69-2CD2802702B8" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Amblycirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Amblycirrhitus hubbardi Schultz 1943:132" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hubbardi">hubbardi</taxonomicName>
as a new species in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4E7B7AAB22DEFC6B767731F7CDCE90D7" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A7B68FE2-7E5D-4D15-BFA4-EE2E8BD8F54C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Amblycirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Amblycirrhitus Gill 1862:105" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Amblycirrhitus</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F558F810871DC1CDAFF0A94A8458E611" pageNumber="3">
Watanabe (1949) described 
<taxonomicName id="85461A51E0CC552274C6E62B66177E0E" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8095F6CC-F238-412C-89EA-58A9087C3364" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Serranocirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Serranocirrhitus latus Watanabe 1949:18" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="latus">Serranocirrhitus latus</taxonomicName>
as a new genus and species of cirrhitid fish from Okinawa.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="56494C4B6D6CD91B5A109A0E4C6094EC" pageNumber="3">
In a review of western Indian Ocean 
<taxonomicName id="2DBAAC3FBB14846DAAAD70995E316491" family="Cirrhitidae" pageNumber="3" rank="family">Cirrhitidae</taxonomicName>
, Smith (1951) created the genus 
<taxonomicName id="8D8F52CB522DC1D9372876B7772E7843" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8AFD1869-8E1F-4D76-94F8-9387419C91DA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitops Smith 1951:(627) 637" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitops</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName id="7448477627603E6DC4D8A1CBF776032C" authority="Lacepède, 1803" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1803" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciatus">Cirrhites fasciatus Bennett</taxonomicName>
. He mistakenly listed 
<taxonomicName id="C3674BE49E4CC4305FD4FFAD05E90B72" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:75A3E3A4-E289-4809-9A69-2CD2802702B8" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Amblycirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Amblycirrhitus hubbardi Schultz 1943:132" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hubbardi">Amblycirrhitus hubbardi Schultz</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="98E60801D558707C41F6547A781751D3" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciatus">fasciatus</taxonomicName>
. He also described 
<taxonomicName id="2AFCF2B7C5127A0FB2A40F59EC5A8B6B" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8BE7E6F6-576F-4824-9BA1-48C11F507E8A" authority="Smith, 1951" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1951" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Gymnocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Gymnocirrhites Smith 1951:638" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Gymnocirrhites</taxonomicName>
as a new genus, with 
<taxonomicName id="B5ED3D9B2108794CD5CA506BE324F4C4" authority="Lacepède, 1803" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1803" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arcatus">Cirrhites arcatus Cuvier</taxonomicName>
as the type species, adding that it is allied to 
<taxonomicName id="F2FE36D631D291D4D8D40C6A79BFBF94" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Paracirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Paracirrhites</taxonomicName>
but distinct on the basis of lacking scales on the gill membrane and on the snout before the nostrils.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0CEB59469C38976BE8FAB4481D3D36BB" pageNumber="3">
Schultz in Schultz &amp; collaborators (1960) recognized 13 genera in the 
<taxonomicName id="133FEA98EDB3BE5921B0674C0551732D" family="Cirrhitidae" pageNumber="3" rank="family">Cirrhitidae</taxonomicName>
, including 
<taxonomicName id="DD5180FAFD60DA6B2C3F666E426AB340" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2F6B48D5-B8C9-49E2-9393-87E1181F30DA" authority="Jordan, 1907" authorityName="Jordan" authorityYear="1907" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Isobuna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isobuna Jordan 1907:158" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Isobuna</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="22539EF240715EF8196A75C3224B9FE3" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:24979421-3FC5-48B6-B0B5-5B9EBAB16328" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Serranocirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Serranocirrhitus Watanabe 1949:17" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Serranocirrhitus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="FBBD33AB5A31968C1BD7BCE62EB88C05" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3C44979F-8863-4A9F-8276-923CD87238D8" authority="Jenkins, 1903" authorityName="Jenkins" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitoidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitoidea Jenkins 1903:489" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitoidea</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="0F0504B3F49C674F005BCB507339A338" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:610A9D36-A6BE-46D2-9742-4B032894253B" authority="Schultz, 1943" authorityName="Schultz" authorityYear="1943" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Hughichthys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hughichthys Schultz 1943:131, 136" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hughichthys</taxonomicName>
(though indicating that 
<taxonomicName id="DBAD462E2E88391D810CA5A6F6F33C80" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CC926BD0-C0C7-4941-87D0-54080B379A74" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Neocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Neocirrhites Castelnau 1873:101" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Neocirrhites</taxonomicName>
“appears to be related”), and 
<taxonomicName id="EAA9E67E2C6BD251D03400FA9789C65B" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8BE7E6F6-576F-4824-9BA1-48C11F507E8A" authority="Smith, 1951" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1951" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Gymnocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Gymnocirrhites Smith 1951:638" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Gymnocirrhites</taxonomicName>
. He obviously had some doubt of the validity of 
<taxonomicName id="DC14525D98A64046F80F1100B22500FC" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8BE7E6F6-576F-4824-9BA1-48C11F507E8A" authority="Smith, 1951" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1951" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Gymnocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Gymnocirrhites Smith 1951:638" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Gymnocirrhites</taxonomicName>
, stating that Smith (1951) “attaches too much value to the scaly gill membranes.” He noted that a specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="903BB6712077208BEC5D8E3947817BB5" authority="Smith, 1951" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1951" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Gymnocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arcatus">G. arcatus</taxonomicName>
48 mm in SL lacks scales on the gill membranes, but a specimen of 100 mm SL has them. He left 
<taxonomicName id="E8FB03473A6CDFCD6AD1D90D880F8A9E" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:5BF2B80F-9DD4-43F0-822F-2E04167F332E" authority="Jenkins, 1903" authorityName="Jenkins" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitoidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitoidea bimacula Jenkins 1903:489" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bimacula">bimacula</taxonomicName>
in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="E07538D3C377C37107495EDEF538296B" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3C44979F-8863-4A9F-8276-923CD87238D8" authority="Jenkins, 1903" authorityName="Jenkins" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitoidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitoidea Jenkins 1903:489" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitoidea</taxonomicName>
and described a new species, 
<taxonomicName id="F214BE563F93D2E500DFA61184A08073" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7953184B-FD9B-41D9-8B0F-8DC50FE578AE" authority="Jenkins, 1903" authorityName="Jenkins" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitoidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitoidea sexfasciata Schultz 1960:257" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sexfasciata">sexfasciata</taxonomicName>
, in this genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="12E9CBBDCAF8F5A7BCD2A5FE729300F0" pageNumber="3">
Randall (1963) reviewed the family, recognizing 10 genera and 34 species. He discussed 
<taxonomicName id="B658297908E9DAF904394FEAB0714D75" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:24979421-3FC5-48B6-B0B5-5B9EBAB16328" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Serranocirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Serranocirrhitus Watanabe 1949:17" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Serranocirrhitus</taxonomicName>
in a footnote, noting the following noncirrhitid characters: all the pectoral rays unbranched and none thickened, no teeth on the vomer, ctenoid scales, and the configuration of a pomacentrid. He included 
<taxonomicName id="9C1CCBC19D15804E61956DDC1C3F638C" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2F6B48D5-B8C9-49E2-9393-87E1181F30DA" authority="Jordan, 1907" authorityName="Jordan" authorityYear="1907" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Isobuna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isobuna Jordan 1907:158" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Isobuna</taxonomicName>
but stated that it differs from other cirrhitids in having 3 spines on the opercle instead of 2, ctenoid scales, and only 2 rows of scales above the lateral line. He recognized 
<taxonomicName id="64A00E51FC896B6F3B2F3C7AEE40BB9A" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CC926BD0-C0C7-4941-87D0-54080B379A74" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Neocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Neocirrhites Castelnau 1873:101" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Neocirrhites</taxonomicName>
as a valid genus with 
<taxonomicName id="28A39598A337ED49874C64D009A953E5" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:610A9D36-A6BE-46D2-9742-4B032894253B" authority="Schultz, 1943" authorityName="Schultz" authorityYear="1943" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Hughichthys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hughichthys Schultz 1943:131, 136" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hughichthys</taxonomicName>
a synonym, placed 
<taxonomicName id="913F1A5AFB15027A37383B0E1D67DBDC" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8BE7E6F6-576F-4824-9BA1-48C11F507E8A" authority="Smith, 1951" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1951" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Gymnocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Gymnocirrhites Smith 1951:638" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Gymnocirrhites</taxonomicName>
in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="2D37A4C981C9A68AB6226738C1F7748A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Paracirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Paracirrhites</taxonomicName>
, described 
<taxonomicName id="009EFC11F9F1AEDE18CE5CCB0158BB42" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CA98AA32-5CBA-419D-922A-D8D84AA880CE" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Isocirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isocirrhitus Randall 1963:422" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Isocirrhitus</taxonomicName>
as a new genus for Schultz’ 
<taxonomicName id="C6D05D23427A42BE48494A176E1A64EC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Isocirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sexfasciatus">sexfasciata</taxonomicName>
, put 
<taxonomicName id="CDCD9E5F125D3CA9EB514C55BF65C2BF" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hubbardi">hubbardi</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="3C353997D646B363A3B7950039BCB11C" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8AFD1869-8E1F-4D76-94F8-9387419C91DA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitops Smith 1951:(627) 637" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitops</taxonomicName>
, referred 
<taxonomicName id="72F1C3D9AFD45D4E3C7AFD04E443FDD3" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:6AD3621E-4DC7-4F31-A629-D987B190847D" authority="Gill, 1862" authorityName="Gill" authorityYear="1862" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitopsis Gill 1862:109" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitopsis</taxonomicName>
to the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="470A13F37857260BA1B588AB72D4613D" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A7B81F0C-1F8D-4339-A46A-3F2F625784D3" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitichthys Bleeker 1857:3, 39" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitichthys</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="D598AD2BAF1D0B5A121B93EFA0785C53" authority="Mowbray, 1927" authorityName="Mowbray" authorityYear="1927" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Pseudocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudocirrhites</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="7A0C866BDB5A29AAE94BF5BC5BF808F5" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A7B68FE2-7E5D-4D15-BFA4-EE2E8BD8F54C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Amblycirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Amblycirrhitus Gill 1862:105" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Amblycirrhitus</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="23C732DF6E9E4D5DDFF4BF30737AD16F" pageNumber="3">
Randall &amp; Heemstra (1978) reclassified the genera 
<taxonomicName id="880DB10A74E09DBEDEC97BBFAC394425" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:24979421-3FC5-48B6-B0B5-5B9EBAB16328" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Serranocirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Serranocirrhitus Watanabe 1949:17" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Serranocirrhitus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="ED44654A9F1F36B2C155175F7352787F" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2F6B48D5-B8C9-49E2-9393-87E1181F30DA" authority="Jordan, 1907" authorityName="Jordan" authorityYear="1907" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Isobuna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isobuna Jordan 1907:158" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Isobuna</taxonomicName>
in the subfamily Anthiinae of the Serranidae. That these two genera should have been placed in the 
<taxonomicName id="8C8E04D87595C612A598CF93949BB9FC" family="Cirrhitidae" pageNumber="3" rank="family">Cirrhitidae</taxonomicName>
is not as serious an error as it might seem. Jordan &amp; Evermann (1898) wrote with respect to the cirrhitoid fishes, “This family should apparently be placed among the Percoidea near the Serranidae....This group agrees with the Percoidea in most respects, the chief external difference lying in the form of the pectorals,...” They quoted 
<normalizedToken id="C6B27634BE8181C8A57CD47BA49B6E88" originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
’s description of the skeleton of 
<taxonomicName id="A95BEC0A667F0B8C171E7ED10A8E6CFA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Paracirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="forsteri">Paracirrhites forsteri</taxonomicName>
, adding, “Dr. Boulenger finds that the skeleton has much in common (with the Serranidae)”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="81ACBF88777B176CB0EB3FD7D77C38CB" pageNumber="3">
In 1969 the author collected 32 specimens of an undescribed species of cirrhitid from Easter Island that appeared to represent a new genus. The following year he collected two more specimens from Pitcairn Island. Unaware of this material, Lavenberg &amp; 
<normalizedToken id="7925CF29EB33E9F52E91B03ED76CD7FF" originalValue="Yañez">Yanez</normalizedToken>
(1972) described the species as 
<taxonomicName id="79DE66F76650031653C5630089A13848" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wilhelmi">Cirrhitus wilhelmi</taxonomicName>
from one specimen from Easter Island.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D718F73C29128AC169D6612BECF15851" pageNumber="3">Kunio Amaoka requested specimens of the various genera of cirrhitid fishes from the Bishop Museum for a graduate student who planned a phylogenetic study of the family. Specimens were sent, including ones from Easter Island. The student did not complete the study, and the specimens were recently returned by Dr. Amaoka.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="771E1EA8C28F542E952473A74D32AA4D" pageNumber="4">
The present study has confirmed that the Easter Island - Pitcairn specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="7B7CCCF053848CE09F579FE77EB464AA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wilhelmi">wilhelmi</taxonomicName>
represent a new genus. The investigation of other cirrhitids currently placed in 
<taxonomicName id="A48982DC6DC56C5813787C9134D3B602" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitus</taxonomicName>
has revealed two more species that clearly require placement in new monotypic genera. The three new genera are described below after the revised generic key of the family.
</paragraph>
